<2ND_LINE>PM-Shuttle-Schedule,0101</2ND_LINE>
<DATELINE>CAPE CANAVERAL, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here is today's schedule for the
crew of space shuttle Discovery (times EDT):
   5:37 a.m. _ Crew awakens, exercises and has breakfast.
   6:37 a.m. _ Photograph lightning in the atmosphere.
   7:08 a.m. _ Turn on furnace for materials processing experiments.
   8:42 a.m. _ Activate experiment on growing crystaline films.
   10:42 a.m. _ Test affect of weightlessness on the viscosity of
red blood cells.
   12:37 p.m. _ Meal, followed by experiment continuation and
monitoring spacecraft systems.
   6:37 p.m. _ Meal.
   8:37 p.m. _ Start 8-hour sleep period.
