<TEXT>
   Base-stealer Lou Brock, Broadway hoofer Tommy
Tune and club-footed former NFL kicker Tom Dempsey were among the
honorees at a salute ``to the feet that have made America great.''
   Tune, Brock, baseball's all-time major-league stolen-base
leader, and Dempsey, whose 63-yard field goal was the longest in
the National Football League, stood for their awards alongside Aja
Zanova, two-time world figure skating champion; and Liborio
Spangolo, an 80-year-old shoemaker from New York.
