<HEAD>PLO Leader to Visit China</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Palestine Liberation Organization Chairman Yasser
Arafat will arrive in China within the next few days for a working
visit, China's Foreign Ministry said today.
   The ministry, in a statement carried by the official Xinhua News
Agency, said a PLO delegation headed by Arafat will visit China at
the invitation of the Chinese government. It did not say when
Arafat will arrive or how long he will stay.
   No comment was available from the PLO mission in Beijing, which
was closed.
   Arafat will be making his first visit to China, a strong
supporter of Arab causes in the Middle East, since 1985.
   China recognizes the PLO as the only legitimate representative
of the Palestinian people, and says it will not establish
diplomatic ties with Israel until Israel returns land captured in
the 1967 Middle East War.
   Unofficial trade and other contacts with Israel are expanding,
however, and on Tuesday Chinese Foreign Minister Qian Qichen met
his Israeli counterpart Shimon Peres at the United Nations in New
York for talks on the Middle East situation.
