<HEAD>Frost Possible In Wyoming, Colorado; Fog Settles Over Southern
California</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Frost advisories were issued for parts of Wyoming and Colorado
today as fog covered many areas of the nation, dropping visibility
to zero in parts of Southern California.
   Chilly weather also settled elsewhere as temperatures fell to
the 40s in the Plains, the Oklahoma and Texas panhandles, the
northern Rockies and New England.
   Fog lowered visibility to zero at Camp Pendleton, Calif., and to
one-sixteenth of a mile at Long Beach, Calif. It also formed over
the upper Great Lakes, the Ohio Valley, Illinois, the Tennessee
Valley, the central Appalachians and North Carolina, but this fog
was expected to burn off by midmorning.
   Thunderstorms produced locally heavy rain in parts of Texas, and
showers were scattered in parts of Louisiana, Arkansas, Florida,
Colorado, Kansas, Missouri and Kentucky.
   Today's forecast called for showers and thunderstorms in Texas,
the lower Mississippi Valley, the central Gulf Coast region,
southern parts of the middle Mississippi Valley, Alabama, and parts
of Tennessee and New England. Cloudy to partly cloudy skies were
predicted for the central Plains, the upper Mississippi Valley and
the upper Great Lakes. The rest of the country should have mostly
sunny skies.
   Predicted high temperatures: 50s in western Kansas and northern
Maine; 60s in most of New York state, New England, the central
Plains, the central and southern Rockies, Oklahoma, and northwest
Texas; 90s in Southern California and California's and Oregon's
inland valleys; and 100 degrees in the desert Southwest. The
remainder of the nation should have highs in the 70s and 80s.
   The nation's temperatures at 3 a.m. EDT ranged from 32 degrees
at Laramie, Wyo., to 82 at Yuma, Ariz., and Key West, Fla.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 68 cloudy; Boston 50 partly cloudy; Buffalo 56
fair; Charleston, S.C. 69 fair; Cincinnati 65 foggy; Cleveland 58
fair; Detroit 59 foggy; Miami 78 fair; New York 60 cloudy;
Philadelphia 57 cloudy; Pittsburgh 54 fair; Portland, Maine 45
fair; Washington 61 cloudy.
   _Central: Bismarck 46 partly cloudy; Chicago 65 hazy;
Dallas-Fort Worth 59 rain; Denver 41 fair; Des Moines 61 partly
cloudy; Indianapolis 61 foggy; Kansas City 59 partly cloudy;
Minneapolis-St. Paul 59 foggy; Nashville 69 partly cloudy; New
Orleans 73 partly cloudy; St. Louis 70 foggy.
   _West: Albuquerque 48 fair; Anchorage 37 fair; Las Vegas 69
fair; Los Angeles 60 foggy; Phoenix 77 fair; Salt Lake City 50
fair; San Diego 62 foggy; San Francisco 60 fair; Seattle 61 fair.
   _Canada: Montreal 48 cloudy; Toronto 46 partly cloudy.
