<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Deadly Brawl,0142</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Brawl Sets Off Tribal Clash; Two Killed</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NAIROBI, Kenya (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A brawl between five drunken people in a
village in western Tanzania near Lake Tanganyika set off a tribal
clash in which two people died, state-run Radio Tanzania reported.
   Twenty-six houses were set ablaze in the fight between members
of the Hembe and Waha tribes at Sunuka village near the western
town of Kigoma, according to the broadcast monitored in Nairobi on
Thursday.
   Police arrested 38 people after the Monday brawl and said they
were investigating the incident. They said two people were killed
and an unspecified number of others were injured.
   The Waha and the Hembe are two of the East African nation's 122
tribes.
   At least 5,000 people died in tribal massacres in August in
Burundi, a tiny nation northwest of Tanzania.
