<2ND_LINE>AM-Shuttle-Schedule,290</2ND_LINE>
<DATELINE>CAPE CANAVERAL, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here is the schedule for Discovery
astronauts through mission's end (all times EDT):
   SATURDAY:
   4:37 a.m. _ Crew awakens, exercises and eats breakfast, followed
by spacecraft systems checks and experiments testing an infrared
communications system and photographing lightning in the atmosphere.
   7:42 a.m. _ Photograph the horizon at sunrise.
   11:07 a.m. and 12:27 p.m. _ Photograph crystal growth
experiments.
   1:02 p.m. _ Meal.
   2:12 p.m. _ Rehearse reentry procedures, including donning
pressure suits and installing emergency escape system.
   4:42 p.m. _ Protein crystal growth experiment.
   6:07 p.m. Meal.
   7:37 p.m. _ Begin 8-hour sleep.
   SUNDAY:
   3:37 a.m. _ Crew awakens, exercises, eats breakfast and checks
spacecraft systems.
   4:42 a.m. _ Turn off materials processing furnace.
   6:42 a.m. _ Cell separation experiment.
   8:27 a.m. _ Commander and pilot check flight control system for
reentry.
   10:37 a.m. _ Crew holds news conference, answering questions
relayed by Mission Control.
   12:07 p.m. _ Meal.
   1:07 p.m. _ Equipment stowed to prepare for reentry.
   6:22 p.m. _ Turn on materials processing furnace.
   6:30 p.m. _ Meal.
   7:37 p.m. _ Begin 8-hour sleep.
   MONDAY:
   3:37 a.m. _ Crew awakens, eats breakfast and checks spacecraft
systems.
   5:02 a.m. _ Turn off experiments.
   8:54 a.m. _ Close payload bay doors.
   9:24 a.m. _ Astronauts don pressure suits.
   11:31 a.m. _ Ignite engines to start return to Earth.
   12:33 p.m. _ Land at Edwards Air Force Base, Calif.
