<1ST_LINE>r a AM-Sears-CreditCards     09-30 0193</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Sears-Credit Cards,0197</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Sears to Test Visa and MasterCard at Stores</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Sears, Roebuck and Co., the nation's largest
retailer, will go after more affluent customers with a test program
to accept Visa and MasterCard at its stores, and plans to add
American Express next year.
   Beginning next week, customers at four stores in Richmond, Va.,
will be able to use their Visa and MasterCards at Sears, the
company announced Thursday.
   Another four stores _ Sears won't say where _ will be added to
the test program in November, an unidentified Sears spokesman told
the Chicago Sun-Times.
   After Jan. 1, Sears will add 12 Sears department stores and six
of its paint and hardware stores to the program, which by then will
include the American Express card, the spokesman said.
   For now, ``this isn't considered a national rollout of any kind.
We are still in discussions with these companies, and none of the
details have been completed,'' the spokesman said.
   Sears now accepts only two kinds of plastic in its 825 U.S.
stores: Sears' own card and the company's 2-year-old Discover card,
which also can be used in other stores.
