<2ND_LINE>BC-EEC-Inflation,0122</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>EEC Consumer Price Index Rose 3.6 Percent In August</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BRUSSELS, Belgium (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Inflation on the retail side stood at
3.6 percent during August in the European Economic Community,
unchanged from a year ago but up slightly from July, a report
released Friday said.
   The EEC's statistical agency, Eurostat, said the consumer price
index rose 3.4 percent in July. It said the average inflation rate
for the first six months of the year was 2.6 percent.
   Among the EEC's 12 member nations, inflation rate was highest in
Greece, where price levels rose 14 percent in August from the same
month in 1987, and lowest in Belgium, where they rose by slightly
less than 1 percent.
</TEXT>
