<2ND_LINE>PM-Wall Street 10am,0335</2ND_LINE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The stock market was mixed today, levelling off
after Thursday's rally.
   The Dow Jones average of 30 industrials dropped 1.42 to 2,117.89
in the first half hour of trading.
   Gainers outnumbered losers by about 5 to 3 in the overall tally
of New York Stock Exchange-listed issues, with 540 up, 315 down and
498 unchanged.
   Volume on the Big Board came to 23.50 million shares as of 10
a.m. on Wall Street.
   Analysts said many traders were pleased to see stock prices show
signs of life Thursday after a protracted period of little movement
on low volume.
   But they also said many market participants remaineds skeptical
that any fundamental shift had taken place in investors' mood.
   The government reported this morning that the index of leading
economic indicators rose 0.4 percent in August.
   The index, which is designed to detect future economic trends,
has been bouncing around erratically this year, and brokers said
investors were reluctant to infer much from its latest monthly
reading.
   Among actively traded blue chips, International Business
Machines gained [ to 115{; Exxon was unchanged at 45\; American
Express dropped [ to 28{, and Ford Motor slipped [ to 51].
   Cadnetix climbed ~ to 7[ as the most active issue in the
over-the-counter market. Daisy Systems said it was making an
$8-a-share tender offer for control of the company.
   The NYSE's composite index of all its listed common stocks rose
.19 to 153.97. At the American Stock Exchange, the market value
index was up .04 at 300.85.
   On Thursday the Dow Jones industrial average climbed 33.78 to
2,119.31, its highest close since it stood at 2,119.13 on Aug. 5.
   Advancing issues outnumbered declines by more than 5 to 2 on the
NYSE, with 1,063 up, 403 down and 478 unchanged.
   Big Board volume totaled 155.79 million shares, against 113.72
million in the previous session.
