<2ND_LINE>BC-Porsche President,0110</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Ad Exec To Head Porsche's North American Sales</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TROY, Mich. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An advertising executive has been named
president of Porsche AG's North American operations, the automaker
said.
   Porsche said Thursday that Brian Bowler, president of Troy-based
DDB Needham Worldwide agency, will move to Reno, Nev., to take the
helm of Porsche Cars North America on Dec. 1.
   Bowler will be responsible for overall sales operations in North
America, the West German company's biggest market.
   For the first eight months of this year, Porsche sold 11,390 of
its pricey sports cars, down about a third from the same time a
year ago.
</TEXT>
